consult-plots-for-dashboard

The input data

This data comes from the sensors and it arrives in two separate file: bp.csv and hr.csv. I am using finctionality from the tidyverse library to read and manipulate the data. This code includes the renaming of the attributes that arrive with long FIHR code names such as c8867h4 which is the heart rate.

bp<-read_delim("data-raw/bp.txt", delim = " ")  
colnames(bp) <- tolower(make.names(colnames(bp)))

hr<-read_delim("data-raw/hr.txt", delim = " ") 
colnames(hr) <- tolower(make.names(colnames(hr)))

bp2<-bp %>%
  rename(hr=c8867h4, dbp=c271650006, sbp=c271649006) %>%
  arrange(desc(datem))

hr2<-hr %>%
  rename(hr.resting=c40443h4,hr=c8867h4,activity.freq=c82290h8 )

Contents of the Blood pressure (bp2) data set

names(bp2)

data<-data.frame(bp2$datem, bp2$sbp, bp2$dbp)
colnames(data)<-c("Date", "SBP", "DBP")

#adding the reference lines
data %>%
  c3(x='Date') %>%
  grid('y', show=F, lines=data.frame(value=c(85, 95, 110, 135, 150, 180), 
                                     text=c('DBP Stage 1', 'DBP Stage 2', 'DBP Severe',
                                            'SBP Stage 1', 'SBP Stage 2', 'SBP Severe')))

#Heart Rate Plot In this plot we display the HR and the resting HR from Garmin. As multiple measurments are taken during the day it may be necessary to change the dsiplay type, use scatter plot or have a plot that accounts for date time in C3.
